 years ago after a thirty-year career as a police officer in a bedroom community north of Detroit, MI.  Since my retirement I have had plenty of time to devote to my passion for collecting old telephones---a relatively new hobby for me----I have only been at it about five years.','I began collecting telephones quite by accident.  While surfing eBay in search of an old radio I stumbled on a rotary dial Western Electric Model 500.  Once the phone arrived and I heard it ring I was hooked.  Growing up in the late 1950\'s and 1960\'s, I had forgotten how great the loud dual brass ringer gongs sound.  I bought another, then another.  I began to learn about the differences.  Initially my collection included the plastic sets of the 1950\'s and 1960\'s.  But after joining two of the largest U.S. Phone clubs I began to learn about other phones and met other collectors.  Since then my collection has increased with phones from the 1930\'s, including Western Electric B1\'s, D1\'s (commonly referred to as 102\'s and 202\'s), Imperial Phones, Continental Models (factory refurbished and painted to satisfy the demand for colored phones in the mid-1950\'s).  I also own sets made by Stromberg Carlson, North Electric, Automatic Electric, Kellogg and Western Electric Princess phones.  My collection of so-called \"soft plastic\" phones in color (all pre1960) include some very rare colors such as Oxford Gray, Mahogany and Mediterranean Blue.  I have these models in both the Model 500 desk set and many of the hard to find Model 554\'s (the wall phone version of the model 500).  There are still some colors that I do not have so I continue to search.  Much of the fun in collecting is finding the rare telephones and sharing those finds with other collectors or anyone that is interested.\r\n\r\nIn addition to collecting the phones I have also become interested in refurbishing, trying to maintain the original look but cleaning them inside and out to make them fully functional and ready to last another half century or longer.  I may spend many hours on a particular telephone until it looks as close to new as possible.  It is a labor of love and I continue to learn more about the telephones every day.\r\n\r\nIn the future I hope to begin collecting desk stand phones (commonly called Candle Stick phones).','Vintage American Telephones',0,0,'3 times a month','I currently have two blog sites devoted to the Rotary Telephones of the United States.  I enjoy posting information about telephones that I refurbish.  As mentioned earlier, I am a member of the Antique Telephone Collectors Association as well as Telephone Collectors International.\r\n\r\nIn addition to collecting telephones I am also an aviation enthusiast.  I became a licensed Private Pilot in 1995.  I have owned two small airplanes and have accumulated over 500 hours of flight time in several types of aircraft.  My flight time has tapered off in recent years but I plan to once again begin flying for pleasure.  I am a member of the Aircraft Owners & Pilots Association and have been since 1994.\r\nI also spend summers boating and snorkeling.\r\n\r\n',0,NULL,'a:3:{s:8:\"show_age\";b:1;s:6:\"msg_on\";b:1;s:11:\"invite_only\";b:0;}','a:3:{s:7:\"comment\";b:0;s:5:\"buddy\";b:0;s:7:\"message\";b:0;}','2010-02-11 10:43:59','2009-03-18 19:18:35'),(1081,1101,'casual','0000-00-00','m',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',0,0,'','',NULL,NULL,'a:3:{s:8:\"show_age\";b:0;s:6:\"msg_on\";b:0;s:11:\"invite_only\";b:0;}','a:3:{s:7:\"comment\";b:1;s:5:\"buddy\";b:1;s:7:\"message\";b:1;}','0000-00-00 00:00:00','2009-03-20 04:21:01'),(1082,1102,'casual','1988-03-09','m','90210','United States','US','http://tayorsdad.ioffer.com/','I love to collect webkinz virtual items!  ','some of my prized possessions include the red lava, blue dragster etc.','webkinz',0,5000,'5+ times a week','fanatical!',0,NULL,'a:3:{s:8:\"show_age\";b:0;s:6:\"msg_on\";b:1;s:11:\"invite_only\";b:0;}','a:3:{s:7:\"comment\";b:1;s:5:\"buddy\";b:1;s:7:\"message\